OOP:Object Oriented Programming
oop concepts:

features:

1)object:Any entity which has own state and behaviour
ex: pen,paper etc..

2)class:Collection of objects that is called class
ex: human body 

3)abstraction:Hiding internal details ans showing functionalities
ex: Login Page

4)encapsualation:Wrapping up of data or binding of data
ex: Capsule

5)inheritance: when one object acquire all the properties and behaiour of parent class
ex: father-son

6)polymorphism:Many ways to perform anything
ex: road ways

-----------------------
object creation
call value through object via function
--------------------------------------
constructor:when method having a same as a classname

types of constructor
1)default->primary constructor
2)parameterized->secondary constructor

Inheritance:

parent - super - base
child -sub - derived





